# CODEOWNERS — path-based review gate for the DS core and the process layer.
#
# The DS CORE (components + tokens + their generated exports) requires a code-owner
# approval on every PR that touches it. DS CONSUMERS (pages, prototypes, docs) are
# intentionally NOT listed here, so they self-merge once CI is green.
#
# The PROCESS LAYER (skills/ and CLAUDE.md) is also owned: these files encode how the
# repo works — the skill procedures, review gates, and the agent contract — so changes
# to them deserve the same review bar as the DS core.
#
# Enforced via the "protect-main" ruleset ("Require review from Code Owners" is ON;
# @samweinhandl-xplor is a repo collaborator). Both owners are listed on each line so
# either can approve the other's PR — GitHub never lets an author approve their own,
# so a PR touching an owned path always needs the *other* owner.

/docs/assets/css/components/   @MasonMaddy @samweinhandl-xplor
/docs/assets/css/tokens.css    @MasonMaddy @samweinhandl-xplor
/docs/tokens/                  @MasonMaddy @samweinhandl-xplor
/docs/api/                     @MasonMaddy @samweinhandl-xplor
/docs/llms.txt                 @MasonMaddy @samweinhandl-xplor

# Process layer — skill definitions and the agent contract.
/skills/                       @MasonMaddy @samweinhandl-xplor
